===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''subterfuge'''
#An [[indirect]] or [[deceptive]] [[device]] or [[strategem]]; a [[blind]]. Refers especially to war and politics.
#:''The Japanese's '''subterfuge''' in World War II caused the Americans to lose the battle.''
# [[deception|Deception]]; misrepresentation of the true nature of an activity.

'''Origin:''' Late 16th century. Directly or via French from late Latin ''subterfugium'' , from Latin ''subterfugere'' “to flee secretly,” from ''fugere'' 



